dismissalComment.html: he has his man. Two times over. He has hit Crawley's top of off twice in one hour. Sixth over in his first spell on debut, and he gets his third wicket with the second-last ball. That perfect length, outside off, seams back in appreciably, and beats his inside edge

dismissalText.commentary: Ollie Pope lbw b Akash Deep 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: wider on the crease, Pope steps out of the crease, beaten and hit on the pad. Shout for lbw, not given, and the umpire has ruled leg-byes even before 15 seconds elapse. So Rohit takes the review. I still think this might be too high. No it isn't. What a review. Akash Deep is hitting top of leg. What a turnaround in luck. Wide on the crease, some seam in, Pope's inside edge is beaten, hits him on the knee roll. Pope gone for a duck

dismissalText.commentary: Shubman Gill lbw b Shoaib Bashir 38 (65b 6x4 0x6 91m) SR: 58.46

dismissalComment.html: offspinner has got an lbw on the front-foot defensive. This is very rare. Gill has reviewed. It has to either be impacting outside off or missing leg. This is such a rare dismissal because it has turned in sharply to beat the inside edge and he is forward so if it has hit him in line, it has to be missing leg. Well almost. The replays show his front foot is half-cock, which means he hasn't entirely got outside the line. Umpire's call on impact. Well done, Bashir. Well done, umpire.
